Microsoft is set to release an update for Windows 10 next month, according to a report by The Verge. The report stated that the update is currently called the “Windows 10 Spring Creators Update”. The name is a recycle of the Creators Update previously launched by Microsoft, with an official name not yet announced. The Spring Creators Update was found in the latest test builds of the Redstone 5 update. Microsoft did not comment on the reported name or an official release date.